info.abstract:
[Behaviour]
Applies an operator on the whole measure array.

[Parameters]
- input measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- output measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- measure : input measure.
- operator name : type of operator
                    -- 'oph_count' : compute the number of actual values (not missing);
                    -- 'oph_max' : compute the maximum (default);
                    -- 'oph_min' : compute the minimum;
                    -- 'oph_avg' : compute the mean of all elements;
                    -- 'oph_sum' : compute the sum of all elements;
                    -- 'oph_std' : compute the standard deviation;
                    -- "oph_cmoment" : compute the central moment;
                    -- "oph_acmoment" : compute the absolute central moment;
                    -- "oph_rmoment" : compute the raw moment;
                    -- "oph_armoment" : compute the absolute raw moment;
                    -- "oph_quantile" : compute the quantile.
- hierarchy : it defines a hierarchy [not used].
- order : order used in evaluation the moments or value of the quantile in range [0, 1].

[Return type]
Binary-array.

[Examples]
Compute the mean of all elements.
oph_operator('OPH_DOUBLE','OPH_DOUBLE',measure,'OPH_AVG')
